def: A turning point; the principal or highest point; top; summit;crown; apex. Specifically: --(a) (Anat.)
To delay unnecessarily; to while away.Dallying off the time with often skirmishes. Knolles.
One of a pair of small appendages of the lingua or labium ofcertain insects. See Illust. under Hymenoptera.
Birds which are able to run about and obtain their own food assoon as hatched.
Divination by the ashes of the altar on which a victim had beenconsumed in sacrifice.

Quite through; from one extremity to the other of; also, everypart of; as, to search throughout the house.Nor to their idle orbs doth sight appear Of sun, or moon, or star,throughout the year. Milton.
Improper, rude, or uncivil behavior; ill conduct. Addison.
Contraction of only one ventricle of the heart.
Capable of being, or liable to be, overturned or subverted.

Of or pertaining to tartar; derived from, or resembling,tartar. Tartaric acid. (a) An acid widely diffused throughout thevegetable kingdom, as in grapes, mountain-ash berries, etc., andobtained from tartar as a white crystalline substance,C2H2(OH)2.(CO2H)2, having a strong pure acid taste. It is used inmedicine, in dyeing, calico printing, photography, etc., and also asa substitute for lemon juice. Called also dextro-tartaric acid. (b)By extension, any one of the series of isomeric acids (racemic acid,levotartaric acid, inactive tartaric acid) of which tartaric acidproper is the type.
